{{Infobox person | name = Jeremie Berrebi | image = Jeremi Berrebi1.jpg | image_size = 200 | caption = |birth_name = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1978|06|04}} |birth_place = [[Paris]], [[France]] |nationality = [[France|French]] , [[Israelis|Israeli]] | residence = Bnei Brak , [[Israel]] | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = [[Investor]] , [[Business consultant|Business Startup Advisor]] | business associates = Xavier Niel , David Levy | yearsactive = 1994–present | spouse = Rebecca | children = | parents = | known_for = | website = {{URL|http://www.berrebi.org/}} }}
'''Jeremie Berrebi''' (born 4 June 1978) is a [[France|French]]-[[Israelis|Israeli]] [[entrepreneur]] and businessman,<ref>{{cite web|title=The Most Active Angel Investor In The World On Investing Everywhere And Reaching Breakeven Fast|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/kima-ventures-interview-2011-3|publisher=Business Insider|accessdate=1 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Jeremie Berrebi Angel Investor , serial Entrepreneur|url=https://angel.co/jberrebi|publisher=AngelList|accessdate=1 May 2015}}</ref> he is a [[Entrepreneur|co-founder]] of Kima Ventures & active in the investment, [[Private Equity]] & technology industries with more than 360 investments to date.<ref>{{cite news|title=Is Jérémie Berrebi The World’s Most Active Angel?|url=http://www.informilo.com/2014/01/jeremie-berrebi-worlds-most-active-angel/|accessdate=27 January 2014|publisher=Informilo}}</ref> In May 2015, Jeremie Berrebi announced his departure from Kima Ventures, the launch of [http://www.magicalcapital.com Magical Capital], advising [[Family offices]] and corporates on their investments, acquisitions and [[digital transformation]]<ref>{{cite web|title="Certains groupes font des erreurs colossales sur leur transformation digitale", lance Jérémie Berrebi|url=http://www.usine-digitale.fr/editorial/certains-groupes-font-des-erreurs-colossales-sur-leur-transformation-digitale-lance-jeremie-berrebi.N349024|publisher=Usine Digital|accessdate=10 September 2015}}</ref> and joined the [[LetterOne]] Technology advisory board.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jérémie Berrebi Leaves Kima Ventures|url=https://techcrunch.com/2015/05/13/berrebi-leaves-kima/|publisher=TechCrunch|accessdate=17 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=LetterOne Technology appoint Jeremie Berrebi and Gennady Gazin to advisory board|url=http://www.privateequitywire.co.uk/2015/05/26/224051/letterone-technology-appoint-jeremie-berrebi-and-gennady-gazin-advisory-board|accessdate=26 May 2015|work=privateequitywire}}</ref>
==Biography== Jeremie Berrebi was the [[Editor-in-chief|editor]] for ZDNet French in 1996 a French [[Technology journalism|technology news]] agency. In 1997 he co-founded Google news ancestor '''Net2one''' one of the first French internet news provider, later in 2004 Net2one sold to TNS Group (UK). In March 2010 Jeremie Berrebi co-founded with [[Xavier Niel]] the '''Kima Ventures''',<ref>{{cite web|title=French Revolutionary|url=https://www.forbes.com/forbes/2012/0326/billionaires-12-europe-xavier-niel-internet-telecom-french-revolutionary.html|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=1 May 2015}}</ref><ref>[http://www.kimaventures.com/team/ « Team of Kima Ventures »]</ref> a fund dedicated organization to [[Investment|invest]] in 50 to 100 startups a year everywhere in the world.<ref>{{cite web|title=Kima Ventures Will Allow Startups To Raise $150K Within 15 Days Via AngelList|url=https://techcrunch.com/2013/12/04/kima-ventures-will-allow-startups-to-raise-150k-within-15-days-via-angellist/|publisher=Tech Crunch|accessdate=1 May 2015}}</ref>
Jeremie won the Europas Prize of Best European Angel Investor in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Angel or Seed Investor of the Year - Winner is: Xavier Niel & Jeremie Berrebi of Kima Ventures|url=http://theeuropas.com/2014/06/10/the-europas-awards-the-winners/|publisher=The Europas Awards|accessdate=4 May 2015|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150408044317/http://theeuropas.com/2014/06/10/the-europas-awards-the-winners/|archivedate=8 April 2015|df=}}</ref>
