'''Jonathan Løw''' (born 1978 in [[Aarhus]]) is a [[Danish people|Danish]] business owner and speaker. He was nominated as Idealist of the year at "IvaekstPrisen".<ref>[http://www.bureaubiz.dk/Nyheder/Artikler/2013/Uge-46/Jonathan-Loew-nomineret-til-aarets-idealist-med-en-ny-sag Jonathan Løw nomineret til årets idealist - Bureaubiz.dk<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{da icon}}</ref>

He has been part of starting up four companies: [http://borsen.dk/nyheder/virksomheder/artikel/1/291816/utradionelt_projekt_skal_skabe_ivaerksaetter-stjerner.html Listen Louder], [https://www.computerworld.dk/art/159562/gratis-danske-e-boeger-fra-eforlag eForlag.dk], [https://www.dr.dk/nyheder/viden/miljoe/plant-din-blyant-og-husk-paa-miljoeet Sprout Europe] (co-founder) and [[:da:Engodsag.dk|engodsag.dk]]. In 2008 he received the Edison Award by [[Computer World]], as a co-founder of engodsag.dk. The price was given for engodsag.dk's IT-innovations.<ref>[https://www.computerworld.dk/art/33161/unwire-og-tdc-vinder-aarets-e-handelspris Unwire og TDC vinder årets e-handelspris - Computerworld<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{da icon}}</ref><ref>[https://www.computerworld.dk/art/45817/edison-2008-her-er-danmarks-bedste-digitale-id Edison 2008: Her er Danmarks bedste digitale idé - Computerworld<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
<ref>{{cite web|title=Succesfuldt iværksætterikon eller fuld af varm luft?  - InsideBusiness|url=https://ib.dk/succesfuld-ivaerksaetterikon-fuld-varm-luft/|website=InsideBusiness|language=da-DK|date=6 November 2017}}</ref>

Jonathan Løw was named "A Leader celebrating Human Rights" by the Financial Times in 2008, and later the same year he met with actor [[Richard Gere]] to make him ambassador for his company engodsag.dk .<ref>[http://nyhederne.tv2.dk/article.php/id-8990399.html Engodsag.dk vil have Richard Gere | Nyhederne.tv2.dk<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{da icon}}</ref>

In November 2016, Jonathan Løw published the book [http://www.gurubogen.dk GURUBOGEN], in which he collected 100 leading entrepreneurs and leaders and shared their business insights. The contributors to the book included Twitter early-stage investor [[Joichi Ito]] and management gurus [[Otto Scharmer]], [[Simon Sinek]] and [[Edgar Schein]] and others. The book will [https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:6339380532345925632 be published globally] in the Spring of 2018 and include new interviews with people such as [[Blake Mycoskie]], [[Salim Ismail]] and more.

He has appeared as commentator in the radio show "De 6 Hatte" multiple times.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.radio24syv.dk/programmer/de-6-hatte/15302004/de-6-hatte-plinthit/|title=Radio24syv {{!}} De 6 Hatte - Pinstriped |website=www.radio24syv.dk|language=da|access-date=2017-02-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.radio24syv.dk/programmer/de-6-hatte/15160609/de-6-hatte-gurubogen/|title=Radio24syv {{!}} De 6 Hatte - Gurubogen |website=www.radio24syv.dk|language=da|access-date=2017-02-04}}</ref> Internationally Jonathan Løw has appeared in programs such as [https://www.fastleader.net/jonathanlow/ Fast Leader (US)], [https://managemagazine.com/interview/otto-scharmer-the-world-of-today-and-tomorrow/ Manage Magazine] Ivækst and Lederindsigt. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fastleader.net/jonathanlow/|title=Fast Leader {{!}} Podcast |website=www.fastleader.net|language=US|access-date=2017-07-21}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ivaekst.dk/users/jonathan-low/|title=IVÆKST {{!}} Entrepreneurship magazine |website=www.ivaekst.dk|language=da|access-date=2017-07-25}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lederindsigt.dk/konsulenter/jonathan-loew/ |title=Lederindsigt {{!}} Leadership media |website=www.lederindsigt.dk|language=da|access-date=2017-07-25}}</ref> 

Jonathan Løw has previously worked as Head of Online at Bog & idé, Team-Leader at [[KaosPilots|the KaosPilots]] and investment manager at the accelerator and investment fund [https://www.accelerace.dk/ Accelerace]. He is currently the owner of the companies [http://www.jonathanloew.dk Jonathan Løw] (speaking) and [http://www.listenlouder.dk Listen Louder]. Most recently Jonathan Løw founded the AI-business [https://jumpstory.dk JumpStory] - a digital communications company combining copywriters with artificial intelligence. The company received a large million investment from the venture fund [https://www.borean.dk/en/frontpage Borean] in the Summer of 2018, and JumpStory was highlighted as one of the most promising AI-startups in [https://www.forbes.com/sites/heatherfarmbrough/2018/10/31/digitising-medicine-your-remote-doctor-can-see-you-now/#1c78e1da2b6c an article] in the autumn of 2018 by [[Forbes Magazine]].

