'''Alphonsus M. ("Phons") O'Mara''' (13 October 1887<ref>http://humphrysfamilytree.com/OMara/phons.html</ref> – 16 February 1958) was a businessman and [[Irish republicanism|Irish republican]] [[Mayor of Limerick]] 1918-20.<ref>http://www.limerickcity.ie/media/mayoralty%2001.pdf</ref>  O'Mara was a son of [[Stephen O'Mara (senator)|Stephen O'Mara, Snr]], himself a former Mayor of Limerick and briefly an [[Irish Parliamentary Party]] MP.<ref>http://humphrysfamilytree.com/OMara/stephen.html</ref> Phons O'Mara was the brother of another Mayor, [[Stephen M. O'Mara]]. In 1918 he stripped [[Windham Wyndham-Quin, 4th Earl of Dunraven and Mount-Earl]] of the freedom of the City because of Dunraven's support for conscription.<ref>http://humphrysfamilytree.com/OMara/phons.html</ref>  In 1919 he helped negotiate the end of the [[Limerick Soviet]].<ref>http://www.limerickcity.ie/media/Media,3944,en.pdf</ref>  His business activity related to the family bacon business, and he became owner of Donnolly's bacon factory.<ref>http://www.strandhotellimerick.ie/upload/docs/the-strand-history-proof.pdf</ref>

